      },
      "lineNbr": 942,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T20:10:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is kind of funny. It\u0027s *possible* that someone else deliberately encoded a PNG this way. In that case, a client using the recommended color type will get something *slightly* different than what may have been intended. I think the only difference would be if they drew the resulting pixels with a paint that has a color - then it will be tinted by the color. That\u0027s probably fine (and if they want to avoid it they can just use a SK_ColorBLACK).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 942,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 942,
        "endChar": 95
      },
      "revId": "df25718560bb2fc2e9f4e66bbbbeca0867380209",
